  "source": "Lemma:\ngiven: n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. forAll: x is \\set\n  where: x \"in\" n\n  then:\n  . not: n \\:subset:/ x\n. n is? \\(transitive)::set\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Let $n$ be a natural number. Then (a) if $x \\in n$ then $n \\not\\subseteq x$, and (b) $n$ is transitive. Both parts are proved by induction on $n$, and part (b) is the key fact used to show that the successor function on $\\omega$ is injective.\"\nId: \"4a4ef5e7-efa6-47f9-ae9c-aeaa2a9c8b4c\"",
